CAPE TOWN, March 25 – The wife of Inkatha Freedom Party leader Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi, Irene, has died after a long illness, the family said on Monday. “Following a long and difficult illness, Princess Irene passed away peacefully this morning [on Monday] at KwaPhindangene,” the Buthelezi family said. “She leaves behind her husband of almost 67 years, their children Prince Ntuthukoyezwe Zuzifa, Princess Phumzile Nokuphiwa and Princess Sibuyiselwe Angela, and many grandchildren. All are devastated by this loss.”  (ANA)